description: SPDR ETFs - SPDR FTSE Greater China ETF is an exchange traded fund launched and managed by State Street Global Advisors Asia Limited. It invests in the public equity markets of Greater China, which include Hong Kong, Taiwan, Shanghai, Shenzhen, and Singapore. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the stocks of large-cap and mid-cap companies. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of the FTSE Greater China HKD Index, by investing in the stocks of companies as per their weightings in the index. SPDR ETFs - SPDR FTSE Greater China ETF was formed on September 6, 2010 and is domiciled in Hong Kong.
name: SPDR FTSE Greater China ETF
